&lt;p&gt;The correct answer is &lt;u&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Speed&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/u&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Speed&lt;/strong&gt; is a critical factor in many applications, particularly in automation and industrial systems, where rapid processing is essential for efficiency.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;It ensures timely completion of tasks, reduces downtime, and enhances overall productivity.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;In comparison to manual operations, automated systems achieve significantly higher &lt;strong&gt;speed&lt;/strong&gt;, minimizing delays and meeting stringent deadlines.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Technological advancements in computing and machinery have further enhanced the &lt;strong&gt;speed&lt;/strong&gt; of operations, making it a key competitive advantage in various industries.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Thus, among the options provided, &lt;strong&gt;Speed&lt;/strong&gt; stands out as the correct answer due to its importance in achieving operational excellence.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/additional-information-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Additional Information&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Importance of Speed in Automation:&lt;/strong&gt;

	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Enables real-time decision-making and rapid response to dynamic changes in processes.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Enhances customer satisfaction by delivering products and services swiftly.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Supports high-volume production lines, ensuring that demand is met without delays.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Comparison with Other Options:&lt;/strong&gt;
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Automation:&lt;/strong&gt; While automation is essential for efficiency, it is the &lt;strong&gt;speed&lt;/strong&gt; enabled by automation that drives productivity.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Versatility:&lt;/strong&gt; Although versatility is valuable, it does not directly impact operational timelines like &lt;strong&gt;speed&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Accuracy:&lt;/strong&gt; Precision is crucial, but achieving high &lt;strong&gt;speed&lt;/strong&gt; without compromising accuracy is the ultimate goal in modern systems.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Technological Contributions to Speed:&lt;/strong&gt;
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Advances in artificial intelligence and machine learning have significantly improved processing &lt;strong&gt;speed&lt;/strong&gt; in data-driven applications.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;High-speed networks and computing platforms enable faster communication and execution of tasks across industries.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Important Considerations:&lt;/strong&gt;
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Balancing &lt;strong&gt;speed&lt;/strong&gt; with accuracy and safety is critical to avoid errors and ensure reliable operation.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Investing in high-quality equipment and software is essential to achieve optimal &lt;strong&gt;speed&lt;/strong&gt; and efficiency.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;span style=&quot;font-family: var(--bs-body-font-family); font-size: var(--bs-body-font-size); font-weight: var(--bs-body-font-weight); text-align: var(--bs-body-text-align);&quot;&gt;The correct answer is &lt;/span&gt;&lt;u style=&quot;font-family: var(--bs-body-font-family); font-size: var(--bs-body-font-size); font-weight: var(--bs-body-font-weight); text-align: var(--bs-body-text-align);&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;.WAV&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/u&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family: var(--bs-body-font-family); font-size: var(--bs-body-font-size); font-weight: var(--bs-body-font-weight); text-align: var(--bs-body-text-align);&quot;&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span align-items:=&quot;&quot; display:=&quot;&quot; gap:=&quot;&quot; style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;.WAV&lt;/strong&gt; (Waveform Audio File Format) is an audio file format standard for storing an audio bitstream on PCs.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;It is the main sound file format used in &lt;strong&gt;Microsoft PowerPoint&lt;/strong&gt; for embedding and playing sound files.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;WAV files are known for their &lt;strong&gt;high quality&lt;/strong&gt; and &lt;strong&gt;large file size&lt;/strong&gt; as they are uncompressed.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;They are widely used in professional audio applications due to their &lt;strong&gt;lossless nature&lt;/strong&gt;, ensuring no loss of audio quality.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span align-items:=&quot;&quot; display:=&quot;&quot; gap:=&quot;&quot; style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/additional-information-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Additional Information&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;.EXE&lt;/strong&gt;

	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;It stands for &lt;strong&gt;executable file&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;It is used to run programs and applications on Windows OS.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;It is not a sound file format.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;.BIN&lt;/strong&gt;
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;It stands for &lt;strong&gt;binary file&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;It is a file that contains binary data.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;It is often used for firmware updates and other system-related tasks.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;It is not related to audio files.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;.LOG&lt;/strong&gt;
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;It stands for &lt;strong&gt;log file&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;It contains a log of events and messages generated by software applications or systems.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;It is used for debugging and tracking purposes.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;It is not used for audio or multimedia purposes.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;span style=&quot;font-family: var(--bs-body-font-family); font-size: var(--bs-body-font-size); font-weight: var(--bs-body-font-weight); text-align: var(--bs-body-text-align);&quot;&gt;The correct answer is &lt;/span&gt;&lt;u style=&quot;font-family: var(--bs-body-font-family); font-size: var(--bs-body-font-size); font-weight: var(--bs-body-font-weight); text-align: var(--bs-body-text-align);&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;By double clicking on the word&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/u&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family: var(--bs-body-font-family); font-size: var(--bs-body-font-size); font-weight: var(--bs-body-font-weight); text-align: var(--bs-body-text-align);&quot;&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;u style=&quot;font-size: 21px; font-weight: bolder; font-family: var(--bs-body-font-family); text-align: var(--bs-body-text-align);&quot;&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;In Microsoft Word, double-clicking on a word selects the entire word.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;This method is quick and efficient for selecting words without dragging the mouse.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;It is a built-in feature in Microsoft Word to enhance user productivity.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Once selected, the word can be easily formatted, copied, or deleted as required.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/additional-information-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Additional Information&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Clicking Methods in Microsoft Word:&lt;/strong&gt;

	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Single Click:&lt;/strong&gt; Places the cursor at the clicked position.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Double Click:&lt;/strong&gt; Selects the entire word at the clicked position.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Triple Click:&lt;/strong&gt; Selects the entire paragraph where the click is made.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Keyboard Shortcuts:&lt;/strong&gt;
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Ctrl + W:&lt;/strong&gt; Closes the current document window.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Ctrl + V:&lt;/strong&gt; Pastes the content from the clipboard.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Ctrl + A:&lt;/strong&gt; Selects all content in the document.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Ctrl + C:&lt;/strong&gt; Copies the selected content to the clipboard.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Ctrl + X:&lt;/strong&gt; Cuts the selected content to the clipboard.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;span style=&quot;font-family: var(--bs-body-font-family); font-size: var(--bs-body-font-size); font-weight: var(--bs-body-font-weight); text-align: var(--bs-body-text-align);&quot;&gt;The correct answer is &lt;/span&gt;&lt;u style=&quot;font-family: var(--bs-body-font-family); font-size: var(--bs-body-font-size); font-weight: var(--bs-body-font-weight); text-align: var(--bs-body-text-align);&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;To see the appearance of each page before printing&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/u&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family: var(--bs-body-font-family); font-size: var(--bs-body-font-size); font-weight: var(--bs-body-font-weight); text-align: var(--bs-body-text-align);&quot;&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;u style=&quot;font-size: 21px; font-weight: bolder; font-family: var(--bs-body-font-family); text-align: var(--bs-body-text-align);&quot;&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The print preview feature in Microsoft Word allows users to &lt;strong&gt;see the layout and formatting of each page&lt;/strong&gt; of their document before sending it to the printer.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;This feature is particularly useful for &lt;strong&gt;identifying any formatting issues or errors&lt;/strong&gt; that may not be immediately apparent in the regular editing view.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;By using print preview, users can &lt;strong&gt;ensure that their document will be printed exactly as intended&lt;/strong&gt;, without any unexpected surprises.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;It helps in saving paper and ink by &lt;strong&gt;allowing users to make necessary adjustments&lt;/strong&gt; before the actual printing process.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/additional-information-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Additional Information&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Print Preview:&lt;/strong&gt;

	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;The print preview feature is accessible from the &amp;quot;File&amp;quot; menu in Microsoft Word under the &amp;quot;Print&amp;quot; option.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;It displays a representation of how the document will appear when printed, including elements like margins, headers, footers, and page numbers.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Users can zoom in and out to examine specific areas of the document more closely.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;This feature also allows users to navigate through the document page by page to ensure each page is formatted correctly.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Editing in Microsoft Word:&lt;/strong&gt;
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Editing refers to making changes to the content and format of a document.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Common editing tasks include adding or deleting text, changing font styles, and adjusting paragraph alignment.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Editing is typically done in the normal view or print layout view, not in the print preview mode.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Saving a Document:&lt;/strong&gt;
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;To save a document, users can click on the &amp;quot;Save&amp;quot; or &amp;quot;Save As&amp;quot; option under the &amp;quot;File&amp;quot; menu.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Saving ensures that all changes made to the document are stored and can be retrieved later.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Documents can be saved in various formats, including .docx, .pdf, and more.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Emailing a Document:&lt;/strong&gt;
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Microsoft Word allows users to send documents directly through email by using the &amp;quot;Share&amp;quot; feature.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Documents can be attached to an email or shared via OneDrive for easy collaboration.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
